# Here are Basic Notes about Python for Beginners

### Receiving Input ###

### Programmers use 'input()' to take input from the user
name = input("What is your name? ")
print("Hello" + name)

#### Data Types of Python ####

## Integer: A whole number either positive or negative, without decimals, of unlimited length
example = '1'
print(example)

### String: A sequence of characters (A-Z, a-z), for example; 'hello' is a string containing a sequence of characters ('h','e','l','l','o')
ex2 = 'hello'
print(ex2)

### Specific Method for Strings

### For Captializing your first character of string ###
first_name = 'mahad'
namer = first_name.capitalize()
print(namer)

### For Captializing all characters in your string -  It does not modify the original string; instead, it returns a new string with all the characters in uppercase ###
course_code = 'cst8245'
captialize = course_code.upper()
print(captialize)

### For making all characters in your string and lowercase ###
text = "YOOO"
lowered_text = text.lower()
print(lowered_text)  

### For Counting all characters in your string ###
counting = "Sea Soup", "Bacon", "Russia"
counted = counting.count("Sea Soup")
print(counted)

### For checking if a string ends with a specific suffix or not (i.e. True/False) ###
text1 = "Hello, World"

# Check if the string ends with "World!"
result1 = text.endswith("World!")
print(result1)  # Output: True

# Check if the string ends with "world!" (case-sensitive comparison)
result2 = text.endswith("world!")
print(result2)  # Output: False

# Check if the string ends with "Hello"
result3 = text.endswith("Hello")
print(result3)  # Output: False

# Check if the string ends with "!"
result4 = text.endswith("!")
print(result4)  # Output: True
